import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['time'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Time')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of count over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'].plot(kind='hist', bins=26, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of count?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    data = data.groupby('day').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['day'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Day')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the average count per day?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
